      "content": "It's understandable to want to avoid medical costs and wait times. However, ignoring the injury or relying solely on self-care may lead to further damage or complications. If it's not broken, it's still a strained ligament or soft tissue injury that needs proper care. Ice and elevation can help, but keeping it elevated and icing it every hour may not be enough to resolve the issue on its own.",
